    "Researchers observed caregivers who cherish routines, a rumor that could smear a clinic, allegations that impute negligence, and staff adept at emergency response. The observations are documented, but the study did not compare clinics without rumors. It can retain the behavioral record while leaving provisional the explanation that reputational threat caused the improved response.",
